---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title={'Pricing — Goldfin Group'} description={'Clear, aligned compensation explained plainly: advisory fees, included planning and coordination, and flat-fee engagements. Fiduciary, transparent, no surprises.'} path={'/pricing'}>
<div class="pagehead">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Pricing</p>
    <h1>Clear, aligned, <em>and worth more than it costs.</em></h1>
    <p class="lead">The families we serve don't want to be sold or surprised. So here's how we work and how we're paid, in plain language, before you ever pick up the phone.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Goldfin works with a deliberately small number of families, which means the relationship is built around access and judgment, not transactions. Our compensation is structured to keep our interests aligned with yours: when your wealth and your family's position improve, so does the relationship. We are a fiduciary, legally obligated to put your interests first, and we'll always tell you plainly how we're paid for any part of the work.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="num-steps">
      <div class="step"><div class="n">01</div><div><h3>Advisory fee on assets we manage</h3><p>For the portion of your wealth we directly manage, we charge a transparent annual fee as a percentage of those assets, billed quarterly. The rate is discussed openly and depends on the size and complexity of the relationship. This is the core of how we're compensated, and it scales down as a percentage as the relationship grows.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="n">02</div><div><h3>Planning and coordination, included</h3><p>The quarterback work, coordinating your CPA, attorney, and deal team, the Proactive Planning Sessions, the multi-generational planning, the 10pm call before a deal moves, is part of the relationship, not a separate invoice. Coordination is where much of the value lives, so it isn't treated as an add-on.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="n">03</div><div><h3>Flat-fee planning, when it fits better</h3><p>For families who want the strategy and coordination before there are assets to manage, or who prefer it, we offer defined-scope planning engagements for a flat fee agreed in advance. No surprises, no obligation to move your accounts.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="n">04</div><div><h3>What we never do</h3><p>No commissions dressed up as advice. No products pushed for our benefit. No phone tree, no junior account manager you've never met. You'll always know what you're paying and why.</p></div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:40px">
      <p><strong>Is it worth it?</strong> The clearest way to think about cost is against what's at stake. On a $7M–$70M business sale, the decisions we coordinate, deal structure, tax timing, estate moves, the post-sale plan, routinely move seven figures. The fee is a fraction of the value a well-coordinated exit protects. The families who feel best about working with us tend to measure it that way.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:44px">
      <a class="btn btn-gold" href="/book">Book a 15-minute call</a>
      <span class="quiet">We'll walk through exactly what a relationship would look like, and what it would cost, for your situation.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
